# Test pad to delete

Sandbox chapter for testing scripts outside main writing if necessary

# Introduction {#intro}

You can label chapter and section titles using `{#label}` after them, e.g., we can reference Chapter \@ref(intro).
If you do not manually label them, there will be automatic labels anyway, e.g., Chapter \@ref(methods).

## Figures and Tables {.panelset}

### Figures

Figures and tables with captions will be placed in `figure` and `table` environments, respectively.


::: {.cell layout-align="center" fig.asp='0.75' hash='15-test-chapter_cache/html/nice-fig_50e58cdf9f66fc725f9a56c77116b33e'}

```{.r .cell-code}
par(mar = c(4, 4, .1, .1))
plot(pressure, type = 'b', pch = 19)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![Here is a nice figure!](15-test-chapter_files/figure-html/nice-fig-1.png){fig-align='center' width=80%}
:::
:::


### Tables

Reference a figure by its code chunk label with the `fig:` prefix, e.g., see Figure \@ref(fig:nice-fig).
Similarly, you can reference tables generated from `knitr::kable()`, e.g., see Table \@ref(tab:nice-tab).


::: {.cell hash='15-test-chapter_cache/html/nice-tab_f9363b50accdba339c849101d0fc1273'}

```{.r .cell-code}
knitr::kable(
  head(iris, 20), caption = 'Here is a nice table!',
  booktabs = TRUE
)
```
